==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aʊzi|-aʊzi]]

===Adjective===
'''lousy'''
# Remarkably bad; of poor quality, dirty, or underhanded.
#* ''No offense, but your cooking is '''lousy'''''.
# Infested with [[lice]].

In the first half of the 20th century, it was highly offensive insult.
Now considered a rather mild term.

